WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.734 --> 00:00:15.620
My best friend recently had a baby.
我的最好朋友最近生了一个孩子。

2
00:00:17.057 --> 00:00:18.783
And when I met him,
当我遇到他时，

3
00:00:18.807 --> 00:00:24.765
I was in awe of witnessing this tiny, beautiful being enter into our lives.
我对目睹这个美丽的小人儿 进入我们的生活感到敬畏。

4
00:00:25.754 --> 00:00:30.746
I also had this realization that he wasn't just entering our lives,
我也意识到， 他不只是进入我们的生活，

5
00:00:30.770 --> 00:00:32.407
he was entering the world --
他正在进入这个世界——

6
00:00:33.202 --> 00:00:38.068
this crazy world that, especially now, feels so incredibly challenging.
这个疯狂的世界，特别是现在， 让人感到难以置信的充满挑战。

7
00:00:39.357 --> 00:00:43.846
I spend a lot time in my work talking to people about who we are,
我在工作上花费了很多时间 和人交流我们是谁，

8
00:00:43.870 --> 00:00:45.336
who we must be
我们必须是谁，

9
00:00:45.360 --> 00:00:47.438
and what our healing looks like.
和我们情感的愈合是什么样子。

10
00:00:48.147 --> 00:00:50.576
So the first time I held him,
我第一次抱着他，

11
00:00:50.600 --> 00:00:52.092
I had my pep talk ready.
我已经准备好了该说什么。

12
00:00:52.738 --> 00:00:56.648
You know, I wanted him to know that the way we find our strength
我想让他知道我们是通过挑战

13
00:00:56.672 --> 00:00:58.226
is through our challenges.
才获得了力量。

14
00:00:58.250 --> 00:01:00.900
I wanted him to know that we can all do something big
我想让他知道， 我们都可以做一些大事，

15
00:01:00.924 --> 00:01:02.115
when we start small.
积少成多。

16
00:01:02.139 --> 00:01:05.582
I wanted him to know that each of us is more resilient
我想让他知道， 每个人都可以比自己想象的

17
00:01:05.606 --> 00:01:07.277
than we could ever imagine.
更坚强，更有韧性。

18
00:01:08.062 --> 00:01:10.340
So here I am holding little Thelonious.
图片是我抱着小小的特洛纽斯。

19
00:01:11.053 --> 00:01:12.752
I look down at him,
我低头看着他，

20
00:01:13.394 --> 00:01:14.713
and it hits me:
心都要融化了：

21
00:01:15.764 --> 00:01:16.915
he's a baby.
他是一个婴儿。

22
00:01:16.939 --> 00:01:17.940
(Laughter)
（笑声）

23
00:01:17.964 --> 00:01:20.901
He's not going to understand a single word I say to him.
他不会理解我对他说的任何一个字。

24
00:01:21.934 --> 00:01:24.630
So instead, I thought it would probably be a better idea
所以，如果我回家写下来

25
00:01:24.654 --> 00:01:25.909
if I went home and wrote.
可能更好。

26
00:01:25.933 --> 00:01:28.389
So, this is for grownups,
这是给成年人的，

27
00:01:28.413 --> 00:01:31.810
but it's also for Thelonious,
但也是给特洛纽斯的，

28
00:01:31.834 --> 00:01:33.456
when he's old enough to read it:
当他年纪大到可以阅读时：

29
00:01:36.588 --> 00:01:38.631
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

30
00:01:39.366 --> 00:01:40.862
"Be a better person."
“做一个更好的人。”

31
00:01:42.357 --> 00:01:44.693
Do not be afraid to say, "Yes."
不要害怕说“是的”。

32
00:01:44.693 --> 00:01:47.477
Start by being a better listener.
从做一个更好的倾听者开始。

33
00:01:49.034 --> 00:01:51.981
Start by being better at walking down the street.
从在街上走一走开始。

34
00:01:52.367 --> 00:01:53.742
See people.
看看周围的人，

35
00:01:53.766 --> 00:01:55.242
Say, "Hello."
跟他们问好。

36
00:01:55.266 --> 00:01:58.377
Ask how they are doing and listen to what they say.
问问他们在做什么， 听听他们说什么。

37
00:01:59.153 --> 00:02:01.379
Start by being a better friend,
开始做一个更好的朋友，

38
00:02:01.403 --> 00:02:04.263
a better parent, a better child to your parents;
一个更好的家长，一个更好的孩子；

39
00:02:04.287 --> 00:02:07.361
a better sibling, a better lover, a better partner.
一个更好的兄弟姐妹， 一个更好的情人，一个更好的伴侣。

40
00:02:07.742 --> 00:02:10.609
Start by being a better neighbor.
开始成为一个更好的邻居。

41
00:02:10.633 --> 00:02:13.975
Meet someone you do not know, and get to know them.
认识一个你不认识的人，并了解他们。

42
00:02:15.062 --> 00:02:16.709
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

43
00:02:17.294 --> 00:02:18.842
"What are you going to do?"
“你要做什么事？”

44
00:02:19.734 --> 00:02:21.759
Do not be afraid to say,
不要害怕说，

45
00:02:21.783 --> 00:02:24.546
"I know I can't do everything,
“我知道我不能做所有事情，

46
00:02:24.570 --> 00:02:26.778
but I can do something."
但我可以做一点点。 ”

47
00:02:27.305 --> 00:02:29.517
Walk into more rooms saying,
走进更多的房间说，

48
00:02:29.541 --> 00:02:30.960
"I'm here to help."
“我是来帮忙的。”

49
00:02:31.510 --> 00:02:33.755
Become intimate with generosity.
变得亲切慷慨。

50
00:02:34.106 --> 00:02:37.615
Give what you can give, and do what you can do.
给你可以给的东西， 做你能做的事情。

51
00:02:37.639 --> 00:02:40.209
Give dollars, give cents, give your time,
给美元，给美分，给你的时间，

52
00:02:40.233 --> 00:02:41.791
give your love,
给你的爱，

53
00:02:41.815 --> 00:02:43.680
give your heart, give your spirit.
奉献你的心，奉献你的精神。

54
00:02:44.910 --> 00:02:46.853
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

55
00:02:48.336 --> 00:02:50.628
"We need peace."
“我们需要和平。”

56
00:02:51.724 --> 00:02:53.557
Find your peace within,
在内心找到你的和平，

57
00:02:54.124 --> 00:02:55.818
hold it sacred,
保持它神圣，

58
00:02:55.842 --> 00:02:58.479
bring it with you everywhere you go.
无论你走到哪里都要带着它。

59
00:02:58.849 --> 00:03:02.809
Peace cannot be shared or created with others
和平只能从人的内心产生，

60
00:03:02.833 --> 00:03:05.409
if we cannot first generate it within.
不能与他人分享或创造。

61
00:03:06.038 --> 00:03:07.650
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

62
00:03:07.674 --> 00:03:09.439
"They are the enemy."
“他们是敌人。”

63
00:03:10.177 --> 00:03:11.520
Love enough to know
爱会让你知道，

64
00:03:11.544 --> 00:03:14.553
that just because someone disagrees with you,
持有不同意见的人，

65
00:03:14.577 --> 00:03:16.400
it does not make them your enemy.
并不一定是你的敌人。

66
00:03:16.829 --> 00:03:18.679
You may not win an argument,
你可能不会赢得争论，

67
00:03:18.703 --> 00:03:20.718
you may not change a mind,
你未必能改变别人的意向，

68
00:03:20.742 --> 00:03:22.643
but if you choose to,
但如果你选择这么做，

69
00:03:22.667 --> 00:03:27.579
you can always achieve the triumph of radical empathy --
你总是可以获得 同理心的彻底胜利 ——

70
00:03:27.603 --> 00:03:29.836
an understanding of the heart.
对心的理解。

71
00:03:31.144 --> 00:03:33.023
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

72
00:03:33.785 --> 00:03:35.439
"We need justice."
“我们需要公正。”

73
00:03:36.774 --> 00:03:37.924
Investigate.
调查一下。

74
00:03:38.623 --> 00:03:41.431
Find truth beyond the stories you are told.
发现你所讲的故事之外的真相，

75
00:03:41.832 --> 00:03:44.388
Find truth beyond the way things seem.
发现事情似乎超出事实的真相。

76
00:03:44.830 --> 00:03:46.069
Ask, "Why?"
问，“为什么？”

77
00:03:46.576 --> 00:03:48.243
Ask, "Is this fair?"
问：“这公平吗？”

78
00:03:48.614 --> 00:03:50.789
Ask, "How did we get here?"
问：“我们怎么到这里来的？”

79
00:03:51.308 --> 00:03:53.160
Do this with compassion.
用同情心来做这件事，

80
00:03:53.729 --> 00:03:55.503
Do this with forgiveness.
用宽恕心来做这件事。

81
00:03:56.003 --> 00:03:58.091
Learn to forgive others.
学会原谅别人，

82
00:03:58.851 --> 00:04:02.103
Start by truly learning how to forgive yourself.
先开始正确地学习如何原谅自己。

83
00:04:02.891 --> 00:04:05.135
We are all more than our mistakes.
我们不仅是我们的错误，

84
00:04:06.007 --> 00:04:08.960
We are all more than who we were yesterday.
也不仅是昨天的我们。

85
00:04:09.370 --> 00:04:12.022
We are all deserving of our dignity.
我们都应该得到尊严。

86
00:04:12.842 --> 00:04:14.609
See yourself in others.
通过别人看见你自己。

87
00:04:15.105 --> 00:04:18.089
Recognize that your justice is my justice,
认识到你的公正就是我的公正，

88
00:04:18.113 --> 00:04:19.705
and mine is yours.
而我的也是你的。

89
00:04:19.729 --> 00:04:24.641
There can be no liberation for one of us if the other is not free.
如果其他人得不到自由， 我们任何一个人都不能得到解放。

90
00:04:25.200 --> 00:04:27.523
(Applause)
（掌声）

91
00:04:28.034 --> 00:04:30.602
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

92
00:04:30.626 --> 00:04:32.164
"I am violent."
“我很暴力。”

93
00:04:32.834 --> 00:04:34.670
Respond by saying,
可以这样回应，

94
00:04:34.694 --> 00:04:35.875
"I am not.
“我不是。

95
00:04:36.368 --> 00:04:39.773
Not with my words and not with my actions."
我的话和我的行为都不暴力。 ”

96
00:04:41.009 --> 00:04:42.259
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

97
00:04:42.283 --> 00:04:43.860
"We need to heal the planet."
“我们需要治愈这个星球。”

98
00:04:44.815 --> 00:04:48.100
Start by saying, "No, thank you. I don't need a plastic bag."
回答说：“不，谢谢。 我不需要塑料袋。 ”

99
00:04:48.124 --> 00:04:50.168
Recycle, reuse.
回收，再利用。

100
00:04:50.192 --> 00:04:54.311
Start by picking up one piece of trash on your block.
从你的街区拣起一块垃圾开始。

101
00:04:55.176 --> 00:04:56.793
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

102
00:04:57.401 --> 00:04:59.420
"There are too many problems."
“问题太多了。”

103
00:05:00.235 --> 00:05:02.991
Do not be afraid to be a part of the solutions.
不要害怕成为解决方案的一部分。

104
00:05:03.685 --> 00:05:05.784
Start by discussing the issues.
从讨论问题开始。

105
00:05:06.184 --> 00:05:09.798
We cannot overcome what we ignore.
我们无法战胜我们忽视的东西。

106
00:05:10.361 --> 00:05:12.321
The more we talk about things,
我们越谈论事情，

107
00:05:12.345 --> 00:05:15.591
the more we see that the issues are connected
我们看到的问题就越多，

108
00:05:15.615 --> 00:05:17.745
because we are connected.
因为我们相互联系着。

109
00:05:18.366 --> 00:05:20.077
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

110
00:05:20.101 --> 00:05:21.852
"We need to end racism."
“我们需要结束种族歧视。”

111
00:05:22.407 --> 00:05:25.342
Start by healing it in your own family.
先从自己的家庭治愈开始。

112
00:05:25.988 --> 00:05:27.648
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

113
00:05:27.672 --> 00:05:30.194
"How do we speak to bias and bigotry?"
“我们怎么解决偏见和偏执？

114
00:05:30.753 --> 00:05:35.519
Start by having the first conversation at your own kitchen table.
首先在自己的餐桌上 进行第一次谈话。

115
00:05:36.689 --> 00:05:38.407
The world will say to you,
世界会对你说，

116
00:05:38.864 --> 00:05:40.629
"There is so much hate."
“有太多的仇恨。”

117
00:05:41.388 --> 00:05:43.112
Devote yourself to love.
献身于爱。

118
00:05:43.842 --> 00:05:47.929
Love yourself so much that you can love others
爱自己，才可以

119
00:05:47.953 --> 00:05:50.771
without barriers and without judgment.
没有偏见，没有歧视的爱别人。

120
00:05:51.721 --> 00:05:55.992
When the world asks us big questions that require big answers,
当世界向我们提出需要 重大答案的重大问题时，

121
00:05:56.016 --> 00:05:57.438
we have two options.
我们有两个选择。

122
00:05:57.833 --> 00:06:02.071
One: to feel so overwhelmed or unqualified, we do nothing.
一：感到不知所措或者不能胜任， 我们什么都不做。

123
00:06:02.737 --> 00:06:07.184
Two: to start with one small act and qualify ourselves.
二：从一个小小的行为 开始，并肯定自己。

124
00:06:07.915 --> 00:06:11.170
I am the director of national security,
我是国家安全局局长，

125
00:06:11.580 --> 00:06:12.867
and so are you.
你也是。

126
00:06:13.967 --> 00:06:17.532
Maybe no one appointed us and there were no senate confirmations,
也许没有人任命我们， 没有参议院的确认，

127
00:06:18.136 --> 00:06:20.174
but we can secure a nation.
但我们可以保护一个国家。

128
00:06:20.493 --> 00:06:23.968
When you help just one person to be more secure,
当你帮助让一个人更安全时，

129
00:06:23.992 --> 00:06:26.015
a nation is more secure.
一个国家才会更安全。

130
00:06:26.039 --> 00:06:29.862
With just one outstretched hand that says, "Are you OK?
只用伸出一只手说：“你还好吗？

131
00:06:29.886 --> 00:06:31.729
I am here for you,"
我在这里，

132
00:06:31.753 --> 00:06:35.529
we can transform insecurity into security.
我们可以将不安全转化成为安全。”

133
00:06:36.148 --> 00:06:38.871
We find ourselves saying to the world,
我们发现自己对世界说，

134
00:06:38.895 --> 00:06:41.642
"What should I do?" "What should we do?"
“我该怎么办？” “我们应该做什么？”

135
00:06:41.666 --> 00:06:43.423
The better question might be:
更好的问题可能是：

136
00:06:43.447 --> 00:06:44.743
"How am I showing up?"
“我怎么现身？”

137
00:06:45.213 --> 00:06:48.080
I ask the world for peace,
我要求世界和平，

138
00:06:48.104 --> 00:06:51.261
but do I show up with peace when I see my family and friends?
但是当我看到家人和朋友 的时候是否平和？

139
00:06:51.797 --> 00:06:54.649
I ask the world to end hatred,
我要求世界结束仇恨，

140
00:06:54.673 --> 00:06:58.908
but do I show up with love not only for those I know,
但是我是否会携爱出现， 不仅仅是为我认识的人，

141
00:06:58.932 --> 00:07:00.337
but those I don't know?
还有那些我不认识的人？

142
00:07:00.361 --> 00:07:05.243
Do I show up with love for those whose ideas conflict with my own?
我是否能包容与我自己 的观点相冲突的人？

143
00:07:05.894 --> 00:07:08.243
I ask the world to end suffering,
我要求世界结束痛苦，

144
00:07:08.267 --> 00:07:11.740
but do I show up for those who are suffering on my street corner?
但我是否能帮助那些 在我的街角上受苦的人呢？

145
00:07:12.369 --> 00:07:13.546
We say to the world,
我们对世界说，

146
00:07:13.570 --> 00:07:16.152
"Please change; we need change."
“请改变，我们需要改变。”

147
00:07:16.176 --> 00:07:18.818
But how do we show up to change our own lives?
但是，我们怎样才能 改变自己的生活呢？

148
00:07:18.818 --> 00:07:22.998
How do we show up to change the lives of the people in our communities?
我们如何改善 我们社区人民的生活呢？

149
00:07:24.509 --> 00:07:30.349
James Baldwin said, "Everything now, we must assume is in our own hands;
詹姆斯·鲍德温说：“现在的一切， 我们必须假设在我们自己的手中；

150
00:07:30.373 --> 00:07:32.938
we have no right to assume otherwise."
我们无权有另外的决择。 ”

151
00:07:33.741 --> 00:07:35.471
This has always been true.
这一直是真实的。

152
00:07:35.807 --> 00:07:39.147
No one nominated Harriet Tubman to her purpose,
没有人告诉哈莉特·塔布曼

153
00:07:39.171 --> 00:07:41.632
to her mission, to her courage.
她的勇气、目的和使命。

154
00:07:41.656 --> 00:07:43.719
She did not say, "I'm not a congressman
她没有说：“我不是国会议员

155
00:07:43.743 --> 00:07:45.584
or the president of the United States,
或者美国总统，

156
00:07:45.608 --> 00:07:50.033
so how could I possibly participate in the fight to abolish
那么我怎可能参与到 一个像奴隶制一样大的制度

157
00:07:50.057 --> 00:07:51.881
a system as big as slavery?"
的废除斗争中呢？”

158
00:07:52.313 --> 00:07:56.289
She instead spent 10 years making 19 trips,
她花了十年的时间，出行十九次，

159
00:07:56.313 --> 00:07:58.190
freeing 300 people,
解放了300人，

160
00:07:58.214 --> 00:08:00.092
one group of people at a time.
一次只解放一小群人。

161
00:08:00.742 --> 00:08:03.144
Think about the children of those 300 people,
想想这300个人的

162
00:08:03.168 --> 00:08:06.407
the grandchildren, the great-grandchildren and beyond.
孙子孙女，曾孙子孙女等等。

163
00:08:07.099 --> 00:08:10.889
Our righteous acts create immeasurable ripples
我们的正义行为 在无尽的正义之河中，

164
00:08:10.913 --> 00:08:13.489
in the endless river of justice.
激荡着层层波澜。

165
00:08:14.872 --> 00:08:21.769
Whether it's Hurricane Katrina, Harvey, Irma or Maria, people did not say,
无论是卡特丽娜飓风，哈维， 厄玛还是玛丽亚，人们都没有说，

166
00:08:21.793 --> 00:08:24.516
"There is so much damage. What should I do?"
“有太多的伤害。我该怎么办？ ”

167
00:08:24.540 --> 00:08:26.840
They got to work on what they could do.
他们必须努力工作。

168
00:08:26.864 --> 00:08:28.532
Those with boats got in their boats
那些有船的人进了他们的船，

169
00:08:28.556 --> 00:08:32.078
and started loading in every woman, man and child they came across.
并开始装载他们遇到 的每一个孩子，女人和男人。

170
00:08:32.102 --> 00:08:34.857
Near and far, people gave their dollars,
无论远近，人们都给了他们美元，

171
00:08:34.881 --> 00:08:36.623
they gave their cents,
给了他们美分，

172
00:08:36.647 --> 00:08:38.056
they gave their hearts,
给了他们的心，

173
00:08:38.080 --> 00:08:39.694
they gave their spirit.
给了他们的精神。

174
00:08:40.959 --> 00:08:43.788
We spend so much time
我们花了这么多时间，

175
00:08:43.812 --> 00:08:46.766
thinking we don't have the power to change the world.
认为我们没有改变世界的力量。

176
00:08:47.211 --> 00:08:51.166
We forget that the power to change someone's life is always in our hands.
但我们忘记了改变别人生活 的力量总是在我们手中。

177
00:08:51.814 --> 00:08:56.544
Change-making does not belong to one group of people;
变革并不属于一个群体，

178
00:08:56.568 --> 00:08:58.804
it belongs to all of us.
它属于我们所有人。

179
00:08:59.268 --> 00:09:03.378
You don't have to wait on anyone to tell you
你不必等待任何人告诉你，

180
00:09:03.402 --> 00:09:05.028
that you are in this.
加入进来。

181
00:09:05.515 --> 00:09:06.665
Begin.
开始吧。

182
00:09:07.195 --> 00:09:11.537
Start by doing what you can with what you've got,
从做你所能做的事情开始，

183
00:09:11.561 --> 00:09:12.946
where you are
不论你在哪里，

184
00:09:12.970 --> 00:09:14.609
and in your own way.
用你自己的方式去做。

185
00:09:15.772 --> 00:09:18.260
We don't have to be heroes,
我们不必成为英雄，

186
00:09:18.284 --> 00:09:19.591
wear a uniform,
穿制服，

187
00:09:19.615 --> 00:09:21.238
call ourselves activists
称自己是积极分子

188
00:09:21.262 --> 00:09:23.214
or get elected to participate.
或者当选参加。

189
00:09:23.690 --> 00:09:27.207
We just have to be brave enough to care.
我们必须有足够的勇气去关心别人。

190
00:09:28.814 --> 00:09:32.867
Now, around the time Thelonious was born,
在特洛纽斯出生的时候，

191
00:09:32.891 --> 00:09:36.589
I went to the birthday party of a man named Gene Moretti.
我去参加过一个叫 基因‧莫雷蒂的人的生日派对。

192
00:09:36.589 --> 00:09:39.070
It was his 100th birthday,
这是他的100岁生日，

193
00:09:41.775 --> 00:09:45.558
which means he lived in the United States through the Depression, World War II,
这意味着他经历过大萧条， 第二次世界大战，

194
00:09:45.582 --> 00:09:47.187
the struggle for workers' rights,
争取工人权利的斗争，

195
00:09:47.211 --> 00:09:49.247
the achievement of a woman's right to vote,
实现妇女的选举权，

196
00:09:48.671 --> 00:09:50.069
the Civil Rights Movement,
民权运动，

197
00:09:50.579 --> 00:09:52.273
a man on the moon, the Vietnam War
首次登月，越南战争，

198
00:09:52.297 --> 00:09:54.518
and the election of the first black president.
以及第一位黑人总统当选 的所有重大历史事件。

199
00:09:54.995 --> 00:09:56.773
I sat with him, and I said,
我和他坐在一起，我说：

200
00:09:56.797 --> 00:10:01.659
"Gene, you have lived in America for 100 years.
“基因，你已经在美国生活了100年。

201
00:10:02.516 --> 00:10:05.375
Do you have any advice during these current times?"
你对现状有什么建议吗？ ”

202
00:10:06.551 --> 00:10:09.131
He smiled and said to me simply, "Yes.
他笑了，简单地对我说：“是的。

203
00:10:09.801 --> 00:10:12.950
Be good to as many people as possible."
尽可能对更多的人做更好的事。 ”

204
00:10:14.072 --> 00:10:15.908
And as he danced with my mother,
他和我母亲跳舞，

205
00:10:15.932 --> 00:10:18.181
who is, by the way, half his age,
顺便说一下，她的年龄是他的一半，

206
00:10:18.205 --> 00:10:23.366
in a room full of generations of his family and hundreds of people,
在一个充满了几代人 的家庭和数百人的房间里，

207
00:10:23.390 --> 00:10:27.483
many of whom traveled thousands of miles to be there to celebrate him,
他们中的许多人 从千里之外去为他庆祝。

208
00:10:28.419 --> 00:10:32.077
I realized that he had not just given me advice,
我意识到，他不只是给了我建议，

209
00:10:32.101 --> 00:10:34.404
he had given me the first step
他给了我第一步，

210
00:10:34.428 --> 00:10:37.738
that every single one of us is capable of making
如果我们想要对我们周围的世界

211
00:10:37.762 --> 00:10:41.581
if we want to create a real, wholehearted impact
产生真正的、全心全意的影响， 现在，我们每个人

212
00:10:41.605 --> 00:10:44.138
on the world around us, right now.
都有能力迈出第一步。

213
00:10:44.967 --> 00:10:49.079
"Be good to as many people as possible."
“尽可能对更多的人做更好事。”

214
00:10:49.978 --> 00:10:51.129
Thank you.
谢谢。

215
00:10:51.153 --> 00:10:54.385
(Applause)
（掌声）